# Frontend Instructions

## Core Requirements

- Modular
- Readable
- Scalable

## Performance Rules

- Code splitting
- API optimization
- Reduce JS size
- Avoid heavy libraries
- Import only what is needed

## React Optimization

- Use useMemo and useCallback where needed
- Memoize components when needed
- Use react-virtual where required

## UX Rules

- Premium design
- Smooth transitions
- No layout shifts
- Consistent buttons
- Proper loading states
- Fast feedback on actions

## UI States

- Loading states must always exist
- Empty states → show illustration + CTA
- Error handling using toasts

## Hooks & Reusability

- Define custom hooks where needed
- Build reusable components

## Principles

- Fast > fancy
- Consistency > creativity
- Simplicity > complexity
